# Starfield Studio project config

Copy this file to `.claude/starfield-studio.local.md` at your project root only if you need to move the
skill's working directory. The skill reads it when it starts a job; a missing file just means the default applies.

Format: a simple `key: value` line. Blank lines, `#` comments, and surrounding markdown prose are ignored.

```
# Directory holding this skill's specs, 콘티, and rendered output.
# Project-root-relative or absolute. Default: starfield_studio
asset_root: 00_ASSET/starfield_studio
```

## Keys

| Key | Required | Default | Effect |
|---|---|---|---|
| `asset_root` | no | `starfield_studio` | Base dir for `specs/`, `conti/`, `out/` |

The layout *under* `asset_root` is fixed and not configurable:

```
<asset_root>/specs/<name>.spec.json     # staging intent (the single source of truth)
<asset_root>/conti/<name>.conti.html    # self-contained approval 콘티
<asset_root>/out/<name>_*.gif|.mp4      # rendered output
```

Rendered GIF/MP4 files are binary build artifacts. If `asset_root` lives inside a git repo, consider
gitignoring `<asset_root>/conti/` and `<asset_root>/out/` — both are reproducible from the spec.
